The `waterParticles.ts` pattern is a clean seam: minimal ECS entity interface → pure builder functions sourced from config → tick function that manages emitter lifecycle in ECS. This pattern keeps everything testable without WebGL or React Three Fiber context. The weather system follows the same convention: config drives all tuning values (particle counts, sizes, gravity from spec §36.1), and `tickWeatherParticles` handles create/remove transitions on weather type change.
