`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
Note `resolveParticleCategory` unifies "rain" and "thunderstorm" into the same emitter — thunderstorm lighting comes from a separate system (§36 separates the lightning flash effect). The builder takes `intensity` (0–1 from `WeatherComponent`) and scales `emissionRate` by it, while `maxParticles` stays fixed at the spec budget cap (500/300/100). This means a light drizzle emits 25 particles/s but can never exceed 500 alive at once.
